theorem Topology.interior_inter_frontier_eq_empty {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    interior A ∩ frontier A = (∅ : Set X) := by
  simpa [frontier] using
    Set.inter_diff_self (interior A) (closure A)

theorem Topology.isOpen_of_subset_interior {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X}
    (h : (A : Set X) ⊆ interior A) : IsOpen A := by
  have h₁ : interior A ⊆ A := interior_subset
  have hEq : interior A = A := Set.Subset.antisymm h₁ h
  simpa [hEq] using isOpen_interior

theorem Topology.closure_inter_eq_inter_of_isClosed
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A B : Set X}
    (hA : IsClosed A) (hB : IsClosed B) :
    closure (A ∩ B) = A ∩ B := by
  simpa using (hA.inter hB).closure_eq
